    *   **Example API Endpoint (Node.js/Express):**

    ```javascript
    app.get('/api/employees', async (req, res) => {
      try {
        // Connect to SQL Server
        // Execute SQL query to fetch employees
        // Send the result back as JSON
        res.json(employees);
      } catch (error) {
        console.error(error);
        res.status(500).send('Server error');
      }
    });
    ```

    *   **React Native Fetch Call:**

    ```javascript
    fetch('http://your-server-ip:3000/api/employees')
      .then(response => response.json())
      .then(data => {
        // Update state with employee data
      });
    ```

